==English==

===Noun===
'''polyarchy'''
# A [[government]] by many persons.

#2 a [[goverment]] with elected officials, free and fair elections, inclusive suffrage, rights to run for office, freedom of expression, press, and association. With multiple centers of political power.

#3 a [[Representative gorverment]] with less citizen participation and control than a democracy, and protection for an opulent minority over the majority population.


== Etymology ==
Coined by [[Robert A. Dahl]] the Sterling Professor emeritus of political science at Yale University.

